---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro'
import Eigenvectors from '../../components/Eigenvectors.svelte'
---

<Layout
  back
  title="Eigenvector explorer"
  description="Interactive viewer for the most important eigenvectors of a single-layer image classifier."
>
  <Eigenvectors client:load />

  <!-- Info Alert -->
  <div role="alert" class="alert mt-6 mb-2 bg-gray-100">
    <div class="space-y-3">
      <p>
        Eigenvectors have a different interpretation than heatmaps. The contribution toward the
        output is strictly defined by whether it has positive or negative eigenvalue. Strokes of the
        same color positively interfere while strokes of opposite color negatively interfere. Hence,
        many strokes can be seen as localized edge-detectors.
      </p>
      <p>
        Positive eigenvectors show structure that corresponds to important strokes or proto-digits.
        Negative eigenvectors show 'inhibitory' strokes that would adversely affect the
        classification.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <small class="ml-1">
    Any suggestions for other models/settings?
    <a href="mailto:doomsthomas@gmail.com" class="link link-primary link-hover">Let me know</a>.
  </small>
</Layout>
